{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8fd0f57a-2a94-46e9-9673-29c1414ab9ca","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01KnLeQfw9QC78jjfNEuEtWq","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01XrsZwyS82QJKJYg9t49hQF","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"dotnet --list-sdks 2>/dev/null | tail -1","description":"Check available .NET SDK","initial_wait":10},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Check available .NET SDK"}],"interactionId":"0d1f0b8e-86e8-4287-9d3e-973d0d64f54e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me migrate from xUnit.net v2 to v3:\n\n1. **`.csproj` changes:**\n   - Update `TargetFramework` from `net462` to at least `net472` (xUnit v3 requires .NET 4.7.2+ for .NET Framework, or better yet, use a modern TFM like `net8.0`)\n   - Actually, xUnit v3 drops .NET Framework support entirely. It requires .NET 6+. Let me verify this.\n   - xUnit.net v3: The test runner is now built into the test project itself. You no longer need `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` or `xunit.runner.visualstudio`.\n   - I need to swap out the `xunit` package for `xunit.v3` and change the output type to `Exe` since v3 projects are self-contained executables.\n\n2. **`SampleTests.cs` changes:**\n   - The namespace stays as `Xunit` but now comes from the `xunit.v3` package, and `[Fact]` attributes plus assertions continue to work as before.\n\n3. **`global.json` changes:**\n   - Update the test runner configuration from `VSTest` to use the xUnit v3 runner instead.\n\nFor the migration, I also need to remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` and `xunit.runner.visualstudio`, update the target framework to at least `net8.0` since v3 doesn't support .NET Framework, and configure the runner to use `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` in the global.json.","outputTokens":770,"requestId":"0431:119996:18EF204:1C7180C:69E824A2"},"id":"79417f7e-8745-422d-bc62-9ae203f09195","timestamp":"2026-04-